headline: KLAC Q1 Earnings Call: AI Demand and Advanced Packaging Drive Outperformance Amid Trade Uncertainty
summary: Semiconductor manufacturing equipment maker KLA Corporation (NASDAQ:KLAC) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 29.8% year on year to $3.06 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $3.08 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $8.41 per share was 4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
